Question: Check if fonts are embedded in an existing PDF?: :How can I check if the fonts are embedded in an existing PDF?That is, read an existing PDF and list out the results in a .txt fileI went through the following example:http://itextpdf.com/examples/iia.php?id=287The above example tries to create a new PDF, but I want to read a PDF file and check if the fonts are embedded or not.I am more of a PHP guy so having a hard time to tweak the code. Any help would be appreciated
Please using this api: PrintWriter.write.
Answer:


*

*<<<api>>>: PrintWriter.write

*<<<code>>>:




import java.io.File;
import java.io.FileInputStream;
import java.io.FileOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;

import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.PDDocument;
import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.PDPage;
import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.PDResources;
import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDFont;
import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.font.PDType1Font;

public class EmbeddedFonts {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        String inputFile = "input.pdf";
        String outputFile = "output.txt";

        PDDocument document = PDDocument.load(new File(inputFile));
        PrintWriter writer = new PrintWriter(new FileOutputStream(outputFile));

        for (PDPage page : document.getPages()) {
            PDResources resources = page.getResources();
            for (PDFont font : resources.getFonts()) {
                writer.println(font.getName());
            }
        }

        document.close();
        writer.close();
    }
}




*

*<<<explanation>>>:




The code first loads the input PDF file using PDDocument.load(). Then, it creates a PrintWriter to write the results to the output file.
The code iterates through each page in the PDF document using a for loop. For each page, it gets the resources using getResources() and iterates through the fonts using a for loop. For each font, it writes the font name to the output file using println().
Finally, the code closes the document and the writer.


A: I'm not sure what you mean by "read an existing PDF and check if the fonts are embedded or not".
If you want to check if a font is embedded in a PDF, you can use the getFonts() method of the PDResources class. This method returns a list of all the fonts used in the PDF. If the font you are looking for is in the list, it is embedded in the PDF.
Here is an example of how to use the getFonts() method:
PDDocument document = PDDocument.load(new File("input.pdf"));
PDPage page = document.getPage(0);
PDResources resources = page.getResources();
List<PDFont> fonts = resources.getFonts();
for (PDFont font : fonts) {
    System.out.println(font.getName());
}
document.close();

This code will print out the names of all the fonts used in the first page of the PDF document.
